data.meta_description: Need Eagle Harbor demographics? Get current population, race, age, income & poverty statistics for Eagle Harbor, MI from the US Census Bureau.
data.text:
Sources: United States Census Bureau. 2022 American Community Survey 5-Year Estimates. U.S. Census Bureau, American Community Survey Office. Web. 7 December 2023.

United States Census Bureau. Annual Estimates of the Resident Population: April 1, 2020 to July 1, 2023. U.S. Census Bureau, Population Division. Web. May 2024. http://www.census.gov/.

United States Census Bureau. Annual Estimates of the Resident Population: April 1, 2010 to July 1, 2019. U.S. Census Bureau, Population Division. Web. May 2021. http://www.census.gov/.

United States Census Bureau. "P2 Hispanic or Latino, and Not Hispanic or Latino by Race." 2020 Census State Redistricting Data (Public Law 94-171) Summary File. U.S. Census Bureau, 2020 Census. Web. 12 August 2021. https://www.census.gov/.

Check out our FAQs for more details.

Population

With 228 people, Eagle Harbor is the 1492nd most populated city in the state of Michigan out of 1,520 cities. But watch out, Eagle Harbor, because Rockland with 227 people and Holland township with 221 people are right behind you.

Race & Ethnicity

The largest Eagle Harbor racial/ethnic groups are White (92.1%) followed by Hispanic (3.9%) and Two or More (3.9%).

Median Income

In 2022, the median household income of Eagle Harbor households was $90,625. Eagle Harbor households made slightly more than Wayland township households ($90,604), Emmett households ($90,489), and Lake charter township households ($90,489) . However, 1.9% of Eagle Harbor families live in poverty.

Median Age

The median age for Eagle Harbor residents is 69.0 years young.
